Like most bubbles, I think much of this was founded on the &quot;bigger
fool&quot; theory.  Even people who knew that there was trouble abrewing
would buy and sell paper, hoping not to be left holding it when the
bubble burst.  If they had been buying paper with the expectation of
holding onto it, they would have looked at the risk a lot more
carefully.  That's the free market at work!

